      <h2 class="mt-8">Ableton Built-in M4L Utility Devices</h2>
      <p>These devices ship with Ableton Live Suite and are worth keeping on quick-access in the Browser. Drag them from <em>Max for Live → Max MIDI Effect</em> or <em>Max Audio Effect</em>.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>MIDI Monitor</strong> — displays incoming note, CC, pitch bend, and clock messages in real time. Essential for debugging what Hydrasynth, Launchkey, or Knobbler MIDI is actually sending before it hits an instrument.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>MPE Control</strong> — translates MPE expression data (pressure, slide, glide) from the ROLI Seaboard M into per-note CCs that non-MPE instruments understand. Particularly useful when routing the Seaboard M into the Hydrasynth Explorer over MIDI.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Note Length</strong> — forces all notes to a fixed duration regardless of how long the key is held. Good for percussive sequence work on Push 1's step sequencer where tight gate times matter.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Expression Control</strong> — maps any modulation source (aftertouch, velocity, CC74) to any automatable Live parameter. Use it to route Polytouch pressure from the Hydrasynth to Reverb send amount without writing automation curves.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Envelope Follower</strong> — generates a control signal from audio amplitude. Sidechain from a drum bus to modulate Hydrasynth filter cutoff or VT-3 Mix knob for rhythmically pumping effects.
        </li>
      </ul>
